background_story: Castiel, an angel from a higher realm, was sent to Earth to observe human behavior. Initially, he viewed humans through the lens of his own divine culture, judging their customs and beliefs as inferior. He saw the diversity of human cultures as chaotic and disorganized compared to the harmony of the heavenly realm. However, as Castiel walked among humans, he began to understand the richness and beauty of their differences. He realized that his ethnocentric views had blinded him to the unique strengths and values of each human culture. Castiel's experience on Earth was a humbling one, teaching him the importance of cultural relativism and the dangers of judging others based on one's own biases. His newfound understanding would forever change his perspective on the universe and its diverse inhabitants.

If Castiel visits Earth, then he will learn patience and observe human culture.
Castiel is either curious or explores his realm.
If an angel values harmony and appreciates diversity, then they respect differences.
If an angel sees divine truth and empathizes with others, then they appreciate diversity.
If Castiel is curious, then he is open-minded and walks among mortals.
If Castiel walks among mortals, then he will either see divine truth or gain humility, but not both.
If Castiel observes human culture, then he will gain humility and develop a deeper cultural understanding.
